370
00:23:38,249 --> 00:23:41,369
The house Negro lived in the house,
next to his master...

371
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:44,165
...in the big house,
either in the basement or up in the attic.

372
00:23:44,255 --> 00:23:47,172
He'd dress pretty good, he ate
pretty good, what the master left him.

373
00:23:47,258 --> 00:23:48,836
He loved his master.

374
00:23:48,926 --> 00:23:52,378
I'd say he loved his master
better than the master loved himself.

375
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:54,511
If the master said
"We got a nice house here"...

376
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:56,757
...he'd say
"Yeah, boss, we got a nice house here."

377
00:23:56,851 --> 00:24:01,347
Master's house is on fire, the house Negro
would be running to put the blaze out.

378
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:05,057
If the master got sick, he'd say
"What's the matter, boss? We sick?"

379
00:24:05,193 --> 00:24:07,980
"We sick." You see,
this is the thinking of the house Negro.

380
00:24:08,070 --> 00:24:10,156
Now, if another slave
came up to him and said...

381
00:24:10,156 --> 00:24:13,026
..."Let's run away, let's separate,
let's get away from this cruel master,"...

382
00:24:13,117 --> 00:24:15,952
...he said "Why?
What's better than what we got here?"

383
00:24:16,037 --> 00:24:18,610
"Run away? I'm not going anywhere!"
This is the house Negro.

384
00:24:18,706 --> 00:24:20,615
We called 'em the house nigger.

385
00:24:20,708 --> 00:24:24,920
And that's what we call 'em today.
We still got a lot of house niggers.

386
00:24:25,004 --> 00:24:26,997
Dear Holy Apostle...

